\author{liamoc}
\title{Complete partial order}
\p{A \em{complete partial order} or \em{cpo} (more specifically a \em{directed complete partial order} or \em{dcpo}) is a [poset](dm-0004) where [lubs](dt-0017) exist for the empty set and for all [directed](dt-0010) subsets. That is, a \em{cpo} is a [poset](dm-0004) #{A} such that:
\ol{
  \li{#{A} has a [bottom element](dt-000A) #{\bot \in A}, that is the [lub of the empty set](dt-0019), and}
  \li{#{\bigsqcup X} exists for all [directed](dt-0010) #{X \subseteq A}.}
}
}  